erse realities in which we all must live, these disciplines will find it impossible to so do without a strong concept of the social.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAnthropologyxPhilosophy. 0aReductionism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh1 aBaca, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBastin, Rohan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErnst, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedman, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHart, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIteanu, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJust, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapferer, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapferer, Bruce, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSiikala, Jukka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Christopher C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782387190?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782387190423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782387190/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK